T1  - A Multidimensional Conceptualization of Organizational Corruption Control
AU  - Lange, Donald
Y1  - 2008/07/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2008.32465742
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2008.32465742
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 710
EP  - 729
VL  - 33
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - To enable a better understanding of the similarities, distinctions, frictions, and complementarities among corruption control types and to lay the groundwork for future study of their effectiveness in combination, I set forth a theoretical basis for considering a corruption control type in the context of other corruption control types. I draw from both the organizational control literature and the corruption control literature to conceptually derive an interrelated set of corruption control types, based on their important underlying dimensions and functions.
AB  - To enable a better understanding of the similarities, distinctions, frictions, and complementarities among corruption control types and to lay the groundwork for future study of their effectiveness in combination, I set forth a theoretical basis for considering a corruption control type in the context of other corruption control types. I draw from both the organizational control literature and the corruption control literature to conceptually derive an interrelated set of corruption control types, based on their important underlying dimensions and functions.
